Message 2003 of 4024
I’m going to try and do a better job of remembering our history. You were not always my antagonist. For three decades, we smiled, we laughed, we
cried, we walked on the beach hand- in-hand, we sweated and we snuggled toes together.
The entire time as parents, never with a moment to ourselves as partners. I need to acknowledge our accomplishments and show our long history the
respect and gratitude it deserves.
